NAIL BOMB ACCUSED APPEARS IN COURT<
By Pat Clarke, PA News<
A man accused of nail bomb attacks in London which killed three people and
injured more than 100 others made a brief pre-trial appearance today at the Old
Bailey.<
David Copeland, 22, from Cove near Farnborough, Hampshire, was remanded in
custody to appear again on September 24.<
He faces three murder charges and three charges of causing an explosion with
intent to endanger life in April this year.<
